original: Lewin, Eliasar (Elis) Paltiel, leg. läkare, Göte’borg, f. 19/4/11 i Berlin av dir. Bencion L. o. Fanny Margulis. G. m. Asta Nilsson. — Stud:ex. 30, med. kand. 33’ o. med. lic. 38, allt i Sthlm. Förordn. v. Sandvikens Jernverks sjukv:inrättn. 38, andre undrläk. v. las. i Norrtälje, Piteå, Mariestad o. Falköp., ord. undrläk. o. förste undrläk. v. Falköp. las. 40-46, vik. undrläk. v. Sahlgr. sjukh. kir. avd. sed. 46.
translated: Lewin, Eliasar (Elis) Paltiel, certified physician, Gothenburg, born on April 19, 1911 in Berlin, to director Bencion L. and Fanny Margulis. Married to Asta Nilsson. Completed high school exams in 1930, medical candidate in 1933, and obtained a medical license in 1938, all in Stockholm. Appointed at Sandvikens Jernverks hospital in 1938, assistant physician at hospitals in Norrtälje, Piteå, Mariestad, and Falköping. Promoted to regular assistant physician and first assistant physician at Falköping hospital from 1940 to 1946. Acting assistant physician at Sahlgr. hospital surgical ward since 1946.
